</div>
<p><span id=3D"tablepress-242-description" class=3D"tablepress-table-descri=
ption tablepress-table-description-id-242">Source: Internal Revenue Service=
, =E2=80=9CRevenue Procedure 2024-40.=E2=80=9D</span></p>
<h2>Is Capital Income Tax-Advantaged?</h2>
<p><span class=3D"TextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN=
-US" data-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8=
">The tax treatment of capital income, such as from capital gains, is often=
 viewed as </span></span><a class=3D"Hyperlink SCXW143679738 BCX8" href=3D"=
https://dictionary.cambridge.org/us/dictionary/english/tax-advantaged" targ=
et=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener"><span class=3D"SCXW143679738 BCX8=
"><span class=3D"TextRun Underlined SCXW143679738 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:=
lang=3D"EN-US" data-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW1436=
79738 BCX8" data-ccp-charstyle=3D"Hyperlink">tax-advantaged</span></span></=
span></a><span class=3D"TextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=
=3D"EN-US" data-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW14367973=
8 BCX8">. In practice, however, the opposite is true. When capital gains </=
span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8">accrue</span><span cl=
ass=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8"> from stock holdings, they </span>=
<span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8">represent</span><span clas=
s=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8"> a second layer of tax, as corporate=
 earnings are already subject to </span></span><a class=3D"Hyperlink SCXW14=
3679738 BCX8" href=3D"https://taxfoundation.org/taxedu/glossary/corporate-i=
ncome-tax-cit/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener"><span class=
=3D"TextRun Underlined SCXW143679738 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US=
" data-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8" d=
ata-ccp-charstyle=3D"Hyperlink">corporate income taxes</span></span></a><sp=
an class=3D"TextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US" d=
ata-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW143679738 BCX8">.</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"EOP SCXW143679738 BCX8" data-ccp-props=3D"{&quot;=
134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&=
quot;335557856&quot;:16777215,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;=
:360,&quot;335559740&quot;:240}">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://taxfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/FF649_1.=
png"><img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1274" height=
=3D"968" class=3D"aligncenter size-full wp-image-64580" src=3D"https://taxf=
oundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/FF649_1.png" alt=3D"The capital ga=
ins tax is a double tax on corporate income"></a></p>
<h2>The Impact of a Capital Gains Tax</h2>
<p><span data-contrast=3D"none">Capital gains taxes affect more than just s=
hareholders; there are </span><a href=3D"https://archive.law.upenn.edu/live=
/files/5474-capital-gains-taxation-and-entrepreneurship-march"><span data-c=
ontrast=3D"none">repercussions</span></a><span data-contrast=3D"none"> acro=
ss the entire economy. When multiple layers of tax apply to the same dollar=
, reducing the after-tax return to saving, taxpayers are incentivized to co=
nsume immediately rather than save. Take the following example from our </s=
pan><a href=3D"https://taxfoundation.org/research/all/federal/capital-gains=
-taxes/"><span data-contrast=3D"none">primer</span></a><span data-contrast=
=3D"none">:</span><span data-ccp-props=3D"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quo=
t;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335557856&quot;:16777=
215,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:360,&quot;335559740&quot;=
:240}">&nbsp;</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p><span data-contrast=3D"none">Suppose a person makes $1,000 and pays indi=
vidual income taxes on that income. The person now faces a choice: should I=
 save my after-tax money or should I spend it? Spending it today on a good =
or service would likely result in paying some state or local sales tax. How=
ever, saving it would mean paying an additional layer of tax, such as the c=
apital gains tax, plus the sales tax when the money is eventually used to p=
urchase a good or service. This second layer of tax reduces the potential r=
eturn that a saver can earn on their savings, thus skewing the decision tow=
ard immediate consumption rather than saving. By immediately spending the m=
oney, the second layer of tax can be avoided.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<h2>The Lock-in or Realization Effect</h2>
<p><span class=3D"TextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN=
-US" data-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8=
">Because capital gains are only taxed when realized, taxpayers can choose =
when they pay, which makes capital income significantly more responsive to =
tax changes than other types of income. Higher taxes cause investors to sel=
l their assets less </span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8"=
>frequently</span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8">, which =
leads to </span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8">less tax</=
span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8"> being assessed. This=
 is known as the realization or </span></span><a class=3D"Hyperlink SCXW232=
442335 BCX8" href=3D"https://www.nber.org/papers/w0257" target=3D"_blank" r=
el=3D"noreferrer noopener"><span class=3D"SCXW232442335 BCX8"><span class=
=3D"TextRun Underlined SCXW232442335 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US=
" data-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8" d=
ata-ccp-charstyle=3D"Hyperlink">lock-in effect</span></span></span></a><spa=
n class=3D"TextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US" da=
ta-contrast=3D"none"><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8">, whi=
ch is </span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8">demonstrated<=
/span><span class=3D"NormalTextRun SCXW232442335 BCX8"> in the chart below.=
</span></span></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://taxfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/FF649_2.=
png"><img decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1274" height=3D"968" class=3D"alignce=
nter size-full wp-image-64581" src=3D"https://taxfoundation.org/wp-content/=
uploads/2019/04/FF649_2.png" alt=3D"Capital gains realization rise when max=
imum tax rate on long-term gains falls" loading=3D"lazy"></a></p>
